Provides assessment, preparation, monitoring and education about cancer drug therapy for patients and to BC pharmacy staff that provide oncology medications to cancer patients at the six regional cancer centres in BC. Drugs not provided free at the centre must be purchased at a retail pharmacy. Pharmacists also provide clinical counselling and drug information services, clinical trials support, and clinical services support. All cancer treatment drugs listed on the BC Cancer Drug Benefit List published online is available.

Provides free HIV medication for residents of BC enrolled in the BC Centre for Excellence in HIV/AIDS drug program. Family physicians enroll patients in the program and prescribe the HIV medication.  The medication is provided to the patient from the outpatient pharmacy at St. Paul's Hospital, or from other approved dispensing locations in Victoria, Nanaimo, Kelowna and other community pharmacies.
HOURS: Mon 07:00  - 16:30 ; Tue 07:00  - 19:30 ; Wed 07:00  - 19:30 ; Thu 07:00  - 16:30 ; Fri 07:00  - 16:30 ; Sun; Appointments before 08:00 and after 16:40 take place in the Outpatient Pharmacy. For all other appointments, check in with the Immunodeficiency Clinic reception and wait for the pharmacist.
